cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on the development of a compiler for generating circuits from C source code to execute on FPGAs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computer Science and Architecture (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of data path generation, which falls under the sub-category of Embedded Systems (cs.ET). The paper also mentions the generation of RTL level HDLs, which is related to Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the performance comparison of the generated VHDL code with Xilinx IPs, which is related to Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the synthesis result, which is related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
